The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Friday, April 23, 2004 				 Satyam posts Rs 513cr profit
 OUR BUREAU																								Hyderabad, April 22: Satyam Computer Services Ltd has posted a 47.93 per cent rise in its consolidated net profit at Rs 513.38 crore for the year ended March 31, 2004, as against Rs 347.04 crore in 2002-03.																								While announcing the audited financial results today, Satyam chairman B. Ramalinga Raju said the board has recommended a final dividend of 140 per cent for the financial year 2003-2004, making a total dividend pay out of 200 per cent for the fiscal.																								The total income for the reporting year stood at Rs 2,635.56 crore as against Rs 2,261.54 crore in the previous fiscal, as per the Indian GAAP norms.																								Net profit for the fourth quarter ended March stood at Rs 134.31 crore as against Rs 80.71 crore in the corresponding previous quarter. Income during the reporting quarter stood at Rs 727.74 crore as against Rs 569.34 crore in the year-ago period.																								The revenue growth of 32.32 per cent in the 2003-04 is more than twice the growth achieved in the previous fiscal. The revenue for the fourth quarter exceeded the forecast of Rs 690 crore to Rs 700 crore, Raju said.																								Satyams income from software exports stood at Rs 696.62 crore during the reporting quarter, as against Rs 534.24 crore in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal, while domestic sales accounted for Rs 24 crore compared with Rs 4.18 crore in the year-ago quarter.																								The earnings per share has, however, declined from Rs 4.63 in the third quarter to Rs 4.46 in the fourth quarter due to sharp appreciation of the rupee and the consequent exchange loss. 
